8c03a3c2-a33d-476d-984d-a2f2bd31e9ab.26f2e7e8-5632-4be8-a761-fbd3d982aa93.description=Retrieves the output of a run communication test job. Inputs\: coreHost - The DNS name or IP Address of your SAS core. corePort - The port to connect to your SAS core on. coreProtocol - The protocol to connect to your SAS core with. Either HTTP or HTTPS. coreUsername - The username for host. corePassword - The password for host. coreVersion - The version of SAS to use. jobId - The ID of the Run Communication Test job. separator - The separator used for separating the results. The default value for the separator is a comma (,). Outputs\: serverName - The names of the servers against which the run communication test job was ran. serverID - The IDs of the servers against which the run communication test job was ran. agentReachable - The flags indicating, for each server, if the SA agent is reachable. securityOK - The flags indicating if the encryption and security between each server and the SA core are OK. commandEngine - The flags indicating, for each server, if it can retrieve commands to be executed from the SA core. dataAccessEngine - The flags indicating, for each server, if it can retrieve its stored device information from the SA core. softwareRepository - The flags indicating, for each server, if it can retrieve software and patches from the SA core. machineID - The flags indicating, for each server, if its machine ID matches the one stored in the SA core. reachabilityTime - The reachability time, for each server. lifecycle - The lifecycle of each server. osVersion - The OS version of each server. Responses\: success - The operation has completed successfully. failure - The operation has failed. 8c03a3c2-a33d-476d-984d-a2f2bd31e9ab.2a829987-062f-4218-89e8-bbd9a17162ab.description=
This operation checks whether a string matches another string, using a specific matching rule. The "toMatch" input is the string that is checked for matching the "matchTo" expression. 

Inputs\:
    matchType - The type of match to perform.
Valid values\: Exact Match, Contains, Contains Once, Does Not Contain, Match All Words, Match No Words, Regex
Default value\: Exact Match
    toMatch - The string that is checked for matching.
    matchTo - The string to match against.
Example\: If "matchType" is “RegEx”, the "matchTo" input is a regular expression such as\: ^-?\d+(([\.,]\d+)?)+$. 
    ignoreCase - Specifies whether to ignore case when matching or not.
Valid values\: False, True
Default value\: False

Results\:
    returnResult - This is the primary output. It contains the string "Matches" if the "toMatch" string matches the "matchTo" string. Otherwise, it contains the string "Does Not Match".  

Responses\:
    success - The operation completed as stated in the description.
    failure - The operation completed unsuccessfully.

8c03a3c2-a33d-476d-984d-a2f2bd31e9ab.501a290c-459e-4055-948c-9fcc4f933c72.description=Run communication test on the given SA server or device group. This operation is supported from SA version 9.1 (sas91). Inputs\: coreHost - The DNS name or IP Address of your SAS core. corePort - The port to Connect to your SAS core on. coreProtocol - The protocol to connect to your SAS core with. Either HTTP or HTTPS. coreUsername - The username for host. corePassword - The password for host. coreVersion - The version of SAS to use. attachableName - The names of either the servers, or the device groups, separated by 'separator'. attachableID - The ids of either the servers, or the device groups, separated by 'separator'. If provided, the 'attachableName' will be ignored. attachableType - The type of the attachable items. Can be one of the following values\: SERVER or DEVICE_GROUP. timeout - Timeout in milliseconds, to wait for the job to finish. Default value is 0. separator - The separator used for separating the inputs. The default value for the separator is comma (,). Responses\: success - retrieved successfully failure - failed to retrieve data Returns\: returnResult - The id of the job created. 8c03a3c2-a33d-476d-984d-a2f2bd31e9ab.906909a0-f3cf-427d-98a0-3864a9bc1f50.description=Run communication test on the given SA server or device group.
